com.week6.iterator

Class MyList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.week6.iterator.MyList<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>

    public class MyList<E>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Iterable<E>
    A simple linked list. One may go through this list by advance() until the last position (endpos()) is reached. One also may delete() and add(Object) elements. After advancing it is possible to go back to the beginning by reset().

      • clone

        public MyList<E> clone()
        Clones this MyList. Will create a new independent MyList which actual position lies at the beginning of this MyList. This clone operation also fulfills the optional requirements defined by the Object.clone() operation. NOTE: Inserted elements will not be cloned, due to the fact, that the Object.clone() is protected.
